{
  "stem": "17135.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 179.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "For example, from '38 to '39, the Nazis actively promoted and supported Jews to get out.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Even Eichmann, this murderer, it's known in Vienna that he called on the Jewish community, on the leaders, get them out of here while you can.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Get out.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Get out.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Make every effort.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Sell everything.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Take every penny and-- and get a visa to get out, anywhere in the world.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And people tried to get out.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And so my brother-- the oldest brother-- had a-- a-- an official-- how do you say this-- from the underground Jewish Zionist organization to go illegally to Israel.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And my younger-- the other brother, who was killed in Auschwitz, also was supposed to get out, but for some reason the message that he should go illegally and meet there, and there, and there got lost somehow.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "He got stuck with me.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It was us together.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Now in September the 9th, they arrested only the male Jewish foreign nationals.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "The women were sent-- I wouldn't call it a ghetto-- in a neighborhood where a lot of Jewish people lived.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "They had to move out of the house and to move in a neighborhood where all the Jewish citizens, the women and the children, were concentrated, and they lived there until 1942.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And then after the infamous Wannsee Conference, they were all deported to the ghetto Riga.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "All the Jewish people, the women and children-- little children-- were deported to Riga, while we were still in the concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Now there were cases where people that were in [? concentrate ?]-- by the way, the concentration camp we were sent in was Sachsenhausen near Berlin.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "It's a very-- one of the oldest concentration camps.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
